WEBVTT

00:10.372 --> 00:13.314
LAURA, VOICE-OVER:
A VERY WISE MAN ONCE SAID,

00:13.414 --> 00:17.237
"LIFE IS A SERIES
OF LOSSES,

00:17.337 --> 00:19.118
"BUT LOSSES BREED LESSONS,

00:19.218 --> 00:21.961
AND LESSONS CREATE
BLESSINGS,"

00:22.061 --> 00:26.344
EXCEPT I DON'T THINK HE'D EVER
FELT A LOSS LIKE THIS...

00:28.065 --> 00:32.969
OR MAYBE HE HAD, AND HE WAS
JUST STRONGER THAN ME

00:33.069 --> 00:36.251
'CAUSE THAT'S WHAT I'M
TRYING TO FIND--

00:36.351 --> 00:39.254
MY STRENGTH, FOR ME,

00:39.354 --> 00:42.936
FOR THEM,
FOR EVERYONE.

00:43.036 --> 00:45.898
EXPECTATIONS.

00:45.998 --> 00:48.621
IT'S A DANGEROUS WORD

00:48.721 --> 00:51.263
BECAUSE EXPECTATIONS
OF GRIEF,

00:51.363 --> 00:54.225
EXPECTATIONS OF STRENGTH

00:54.325 --> 00:56.907
CAN OFTEN FORCE US
TO PUSH DOWN

00:57.007 --> 00:59.429
HOW WE'RE TRULY FEELING.

00:59.529 --> 01:03.271
THANK GOD
FOR OUR REAL FRIENDS,

01:03.371 --> 01:05.673
THE ONES WHO SEE US
THROUGH THE VEIL

01:05.773 --> 01:09.436
AND HOLD US ACCOUNTABLE;
NO EXPECTATIONS,

01:09.536 --> 01:12.438
JUST THERE
TO CONSTANTLY REMIND US

01:12.538 --> 01:15.240
THAT THIS ISN'T
OUR FAULT,

01:15.340 --> 01:18.863
EVEN IF OUR PAIN
IS TELLING US OTHERWISE.

01:20.344 --> 01:23.286
BUT IN THOSE
EXTRA-QUIET MOMENTS,

01:23.386 --> 01:26.289
WHEN THE PAIN FROM THE LOSS

01:26.389 --> 01:29.011
BECOMES TOO UNBEARABLE,

01:29.111 --> 01:32.293
AND EVERY OUNCE OF
YOUR SHATTERED HEART
IS SCREAMING,

01:32.393 --> 01:35.295
"WHAT ARE WE GOING TO DO?"

01:35.395 --> 01:38.298
WE FINALLY FIND STRENGTH

01:38.398 --> 01:42.261
IN THE PLACE
YOU LEAST EXPECT.

01:42.361 --> 01:45.463
FEMALE SINGER: ♪ I DON'T WANT
TO BE IN A WORLD ♪

01:45.563 --> 01:54.650
♪ WITHOUT YOU ♪

01:56.891 --> 01:59.273
BILLY ON VOICEMAIL:
SO, I KNOW YOU SAID
YOU NEEDED SOME TIME.

01:59.373 --> 02:02.956
UM, I'M HERE
WHENEVER YOU'RE READY,

02:03.056 --> 02:06.559
UH, BECAUSE, YOU KNOW,
YOU AND ME,

02:06.659 --> 02:09.801
WE GOT ALL THE TIME
IN THE WORLD.

02:09.901 --> 02:11.562
HEY, MAN.

02:11.662 --> 02:14.164
HOW'D YOU KNOW
I WAS HERE?

02:14.264 --> 02:17.167
DILLON: THIS ROOM'S ALWAYS
BEEN YOUR QUIET PLACE.
SPENCER: MM-HMM.

02:17.267 --> 02:20.049
DILLON: YOU OK?
SPENCER: YEAH.
YEAH, I'M STRAIGHT.

02:20.149 --> 02:23.491
WAS THAT COACH BAKER'S VOICE
I HEARD ON THE VOICEMAIL?

02:23.591 --> 02:26.494
LOOK, MAN, IT'S OK

02:26.594 --> 02:29.176
IF YOU'RE NOT OK, SPENCE.

02:29.276 --> 02:33.699
COACH BAKER MEANT
A LOT TO ALL OF US,
BUT WHAT YOU GUYS HAD

02:33.799 --> 02:36.061
WAS SPECIAL...

02:36.161 --> 02:39.023
AND I KNOW YOU.
YOU'RE PROBABLY
SITTING HERE RIGHT NOW

02:39.123 --> 02:42.826
THINKING ABOUT ALL
THE WAYS YOU CAN HELP
EVERYONE ELSE THROUGH THIS,

02:42.926 --> 02:47.089
WHICH IS WHY I'M HERE
TO ASK YOU, HOW CAN I
HELP YOU THROUGH THIS?

02:50.091 --> 02:54.274
I APPRECIATE YOU, D.

02:54.374 --> 02:58.317
MOMS IS PROBABLY WONDERING
WHERE YOU ARE. I'LL LET
HER KNOW YOU'RE WITH ME.

02:58.417 --> 03:00.919
GRACE: HOW DO YOU THINK
HE GOT HERE?
SPENCER: AH.

03:01.019 --> 03:02.921
[DOOR CLOSES]
DILLON: THERE'S NO WAY
WE'RE LETTING YOU

03:03.021 --> 03:05.283
GRIEVE ALONE, MAN.
SPENCER: I'M GOOD.

03:05.383 --> 03:07.364
I'M GOOD, FOR REAL.

03:07.464 --> 03:09.846
NOW, JORDAN, OLIVIA,
MRS. BAKER,

03:09.946 --> 03:12.368
THEM'S THE ONES WE NEED
TO BE LOVING ON.

03:12.468 --> 03:14.369
GRACE: AGREED,

03:14.469 --> 03:17.252
AND WE'LL BE THERE
FOR THEM.

03:17.352 --> 03:19.573
BUT RIGHT NOW,

03:19.673 --> 03:23.216
YOUR MAMA NEED
A BIG OLD HUG FROM HER BOYS.

03:23.316 --> 03:26.638
SPENCER: YEAH.
GRACE: AH.

03:39.728 --> 03:42.230
THANK YOU
FOR, UM...

03:42.330 --> 03:45.353
I KNOW MAKING BEDS
ISN'T YOUR THING.

03:45.453 --> 03:48.755
YEAH, BUT...BEING
BY YOUR SIDE IS,

03:48.855 --> 03:51.717
SO...I'M HAPPY
TO DO THIS.

03:51.817 --> 03:53.559
THANKS.

03:53.659 --> 03:55.980
[CELL PHONE VIBRATES]

04:01.665 --> 04:04.447
IT'S OK IF YOU NEED
TO GET THAT.

04:04.547 --> 04:06.408
NO.

04:06.508 --> 04:08.410
EVERYTHING ELSE
CAN WAIT.

04:08.510 --> 04:10.511
SPENCER: HEY.

04:11.832 --> 04:13.373
HEY.

04:13.473 --> 04:17.657
YOU WERE RIGHT ABOUT
THE WHOLE "BED NOT
BEING MY THING" THING,

04:17.757 --> 04:22.300
SO...I'MMA LET
SPENCE TAKE OVER.

04:22.400 --> 04:24.902
YEAH.

04:25.002 --> 04:27.324
SPENCER: SUBTLE.
PATIENCE: SHUT UP.

04:34.689 --> 04:37.031
HOW YOU HOLDING UP?

04:37.131 --> 04:38.993
SAME.

04:39.093 --> 04:40.314
YOU?

04:40.414 --> 04:43.476
SAME, BUT THIS AIN'T
ABOUT ME RIGHT NOW.

04:43.576 --> 04:45.577
OF COURSE IT IS.

04:47.579 --> 04:49.480
MY DAD WAS...

04:49.580 --> 04:52.242
SUCH A BRIGHT LIGHT.

04:52.342 --> 04:56.125
YOU WERE A HUGE PART
OF THAT LIGHT, SPENCER.

04:56.225 --> 04:58.807
WE ALL WERE...

04:58.907 --> 05:01.449
EVEN JABARI.

05:01.549 --> 05:03.451
YEAH, I SEEN HIM
THIS MORNING.

05:03.551 --> 05:05.332
HE'S WORRIED
ABOUT YOU ALL.

05:05.432 --> 05:07.334
HOW'S HE DOING?

05:07.434 --> 05:08.975
HE'S PRETTY BROKEN UP,

05:09.075 --> 05:12.037
BUT I WANT THE TRUTH ABOUT
HOW YOU REALLY DOING, LIV.

05:15.760 --> 05:19.042
I DON'T KNOW HOW
TO HELP MY MOM.

05:25.767 --> 05:28.109
SHE'S SO LOST
WITHOUT DAD,

05:28.209 --> 05:32.412
AND I CAN'T FIND
THE WORDS TO HELP HER.

05:35.255 --> 05:39.158
I HAVE TO WRITE A EULOGY
FOR A FUNERAL...

05:39.258 --> 05:42.320
[SOBBING]
THAT NONE OF US
ARE READY FOR.

05:42.420 --> 05:46.383
I HAVE NO CLUE WHAT
TO SAY ABOUT HIM.

05:48.584 --> 05:51.447
LOOK, JUST...
[SIGHS]

05:51.547 --> 05:54.529
START WITH SOMETHING
SIMPLE, YOU KNOW?

05:54.629 --> 05:56.490
"MY DAD WAS..."

05:56.590 --> 05:58.532
[SIGHS]
I DON'T KNOW IF I'M READY

05:58.632 --> 06:00.854
TO SAY MY DAD'S NAME
IN THE PAST TENSE.

06:00.954 --> 06:02.995
OK.

06:04.957 --> 06:07.499
"MY DAD IS."

06:07.599 --> 06:09.600
START THERE.

06:11.762 --> 06:14.504
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

06:14.604 --> 06:16.826
HEY.
I'M SO SORRY.

06:16.926 --> 06:18.827
I--I TRIED TO GET HERE
AS FAST AS I COULD,

06:18.927 --> 06:20.869
AND THE TRAFFIC
WAS INSANE.

06:20.969 --> 06:23.711
UM, WERE YOU ABLE TO FIND
YOUR DAD'S BLUE SUIT?

06:23.811 --> 06:25.993
I CAN'T GO IN THERE.

06:26.093 --> 06:28.314
LAYLA: IN WHERE?
JORDAN: HIS CLOSET,

06:28.414 --> 06:32.317
OR ANY--ANY ROOM,
FOR THAT MATTER.
LAYLA: JORDAN.

06:32.417 --> 06:34.999
WE--WE WERE JUST
PLAYING CATCH
AT THE COMBINE,

06:35.099 --> 06:38.342
AND...
HOW IS HE GONE?

06:41.104 --> 06:43.325
I...I SHOULD HAVE
BEEN ON THE BUS.

06:43.425 --> 06:46.368
I SHOULD HAVE BEEN ON THE BUS.
I COULD HAVE SAVED HIM.
LAYLA: NO. HEY, HEY.

06:46.468 --> 06:49.250
I COULD HAVE STOPPED HIM. YOU--
LAYLA: NO, NO, NO. LISTEN TO ME.
LISTEN TO ME.

06:49.350 --> 06:52.252
[JORDAN SIGHS]
LAYLA: OK, LOOK, WHAT YOU'RE...

06:52.352 --> 06:55.495
WHAT YOU'RE FEELING
IS TOTALLY NORMAL, OK?

06:55.595 --> 06:58.337
YOUR HEART'S JUST
NOT READY TO ACCEPT

06:58.437 --> 07:01.059
WHAT THE UNIVERSE DECIDED.

07:01.159 --> 07:03.340
BUT...

07:03.440 --> 07:06.383
YOU STILL HAVE
YOUR DAD'S MEMORY

07:06.483 --> 07:09.225
AND HIS LEGACY,

07:09.325 --> 07:11.426
HIS FAVOURITE BLUE SUIT.

07:11.526 --> 07:13.388
WELL, YOU WILL

07:13.488 --> 07:16.390
ONCE YOU AND I GO
TO HIS CLOSET AND...

07:16.490 --> 07:20.153
AND GET IT TOGETHER,
IF THAT'S OK.

07:20.253 --> 07:21.794
YEAH.

07:21.894 --> 07:23.896
OK.

07:36.145 --> 07:38.226
DENISE: LAURA?

07:39.667 --> 07:41.669
LAURA?

07:42.950 --> 07:46.052
[SETS DOWN MUG]
JUST CHECKING
ON YOU, MAMA.

07:46.152 --> 07:49.475
WE GOT SOME FOOD
COMING SHORTLY, OK?

07:57.481 --> 07:59.582
WHAT ABOUT YOU,
MR. BAKER?

07:59.682 --> 08:02.064
HOW YOU HOLDING UP?

08:02.164 --> 08:04.986
I'VE BEEN STEADY,
FOR THE MOST PART.

08:05.086 --> 08:08.229
IT'S LAURA
I'M WORRIED ABOUT,

08:08.329 --> 08:10.551
AND YOU, TOO, GRACE.

08:10.651 --> 08:13.473
LOSING A CHILD,
LOSING A SPOUSE,

08:13.573 --> 08:15.634
LOSING A BEST FRIEND--

08:15.734 --> 08:18.316
NONE OF IT IS EASY.

08:18.416 --> 08:20.678
I CAN'T LIE.

08:20.778 --> 08:23.660
THIS IS
A DIFFERENT TYPE OF HURT.

08:25.021 --> 08:29.285
BUT I KNOW IT IS
FOR ALL OF US.

08:29.385 --> 08:32.407
YOU KNOW, THE BEST WAY
TO HELP THAT IS TO PLAN

08:32.507 --> 08:34.168
THE PERFECT HOME-GOING
FOR BILLY.

08:34.268 --> 08:37.611
AMEN, SPEAKING OF WHICH,
DO WE HAVE A DATE?

08:37.711 --> 08:40.193
[FRONT DOOR OPENS]

08:48.199 --> 08:50.741
THAT'S NOT
THE RIGHT SUIT, JORDAN.

08:50.841 --> 08:53.583
UH...BUT YOU SAID
TO GET DAD'S
BLUE SUIT.

08:53.683 --> 08:55.784
THIS WAS
THE ONLY BLUE SUIT
IN THE CLOSET.

08:55.884 --> 08:59.147
YES! THAT'S NAVY BLUE!
AND THE ONE I NEED
IS LIGHT BLUE!

08:59.247 --> 09:01.749
IT'S THE ONE
HE WORE THE DAY WE
RENEWED OUR VOWS!

09:01.849 --> 09:03.991
WELL, W-WE CAN
LOOK AGAIN, MOM.
IT'S OK.

09:04.091 --> 09:06.272
SPENCER: YEAH, I'M
DOWN TO HELP, TOO.
[LAURA SIGHS]

09:06.372 --> 09:08.834
LAYLA: I--I WAS WITH
JORDAN, AND I PROMISE

09:08.934 --> 09:10.956
LOOKING AGAIN
WON'T HELP.
THE SUIT WASN'T THERE.

09:11.056 --> 09:13.277
WILLIE: MAYBE IT'S
AT THE CLEANERS?

09:13.377 --> 09:16.600
[LAURA SIGHS]
JORDAN: I'LL CHECK THE CLEANERS.

09:16.700 --> 09:20.843
LAURA: OK.
JORDAN: I...I'M SORRY, MOM.

09:20.943 --> 09:22.805
I'M SORRY.
I SHOULDN'T HAVE SNAPPED.

09:22.905 --> 09:26.848
IT'S JUST THIS IS ALL,
UH...IT'S ALL TOO MUCH--

09:26.948 --> 09:29.490
THE FLOWERS,
GIFT BASKETS, THE FOOD.

09:29.590 --> 09:32.452
IT'S...
[SIGHS]

09:32.552 --> 09:35.134
I JUST WANT TO BURY
MY HUSBAND IN PEACE.

09:35.234 --> 09:37.335
DENISE: AND YOU WILL.
WE'LL MAKE SURE
IT'S PERFECT.

09:37.435 --> 09:41.959
I DON'T WANT PERFECT.
I JUST WANT IT TO BE OVER!

09:43.400 --> 09:45.461
[SIGHS]
TOMORROW, OK?
I PICKED THE DATE.

09:45.561 --> 09:47.623
THE FUNERAL'S TOMORROW.
OLIVIA: TOMORROW? MOM,

09:47.723 --> 09:50.505
THAT WON'T GIVE DAD'S
OUT-OF-STATE FRIENDS ENOUGH--
LAURA: JUST STOP!

09:50.605 --> 09:54.388
[VOICE SHAKING]
I SHARED YOUR FATHER
WITH HIS FOOTBALL TEAMS

09:54.488 --> 09:57.390
AND THE WHOLE DAMN WORLD
FOR MOST OF HIS LIFE,

09:57.490 --> 10:01.634
AND NOW HE'S GONE
AND I DON'T WANT
TO SHARE HIM ANYMORE.

10:01.734 --> 10:05.476
SO THE FUNERAL IS TOMORROW.
FAMILY AND CLOSE FRIENDS ONLY.

10:05.576 --> 10:08.098
OK?
THAT'S MY DECISION.

10:20.828 --> 10:23.570
ASHER:
MY GIRLFRIEND'S PREGNANT, COACH.
BILLY: YOU GOT A BIG HEART.

10:23.670 --> 10:28.514
YOU'RE A GREAT COACH,
AND YOU'LL BE AN EVEN
BETTER FATHER.

10:34.638 --> 10:36.500
JJ: YO, ASH.

10:36.600 --> 10:39.902
DID YOU, UH,
CHECK YOUR TEXTS
FROM SPENCE?

10:40.002 --> 10:43.425
[SNIFFLES]
UH, NO.
EVERYTHING COOL?

10:43.525 --> 10:47.428
YEAH, UH, THEY'RE MOVING
COACH BAKER'S FUNERAL
TO TOMORROW.

10:47.528 --> 10:49.189
WOW. HEH.

10:49.289 --> 10:53.072
A LOT SOONER THAN I
THOUGHT, BUT...OK.

10:53.172 --> 10:56.034
YOU WERE ON THE BUS
WITH COACH BAKER, BRO.

10:56.134 --> 10:58.196
I KNOW THAT'S
WEIGHING ON YOU.

10:58.296 --> 11:00.718
THIS IS JUST
A MENTAL-HEALTH CHECK.

11:00.818 --> 11:02.719
APPRECIATE THAT.

11:02.819 --> 11:04.721
UM...

11:04.821 --> 11:07.683
THANKFUL TO BE ALIVE.

11:07.783 --> 11:10.765
JUST WISH THE OUTCOME
COULD HAVE BEEN DIFFERENT.

11:10.865 --> 11:13.247
I KNOW.

11:13.347 --> 11:14.928
[SCOFFS]

11:15.028 --> 11:18.471
LIFE REALLY IS A GIFT
THAT CAN BE RETURNED
AT ANY TIME.

11:19.832 --> 11:21.853
KNOW THAT COACH BAKER,
HE'D...

11:21.953 --> 11:25.736
WANT ME TO SPIN
THIS CLOSE CALL
INTO A POSITIVE.

11:25.836 --> 11:28.098
ANYTHING I CAN DO
TO HELP?

11:28.198 --> 11:31.421
MAYBE WE BOTH NEED
TO MAKE EVERY DAY COUNT...

11:31.521 --> 11:35.344
ESPECIALLY BY THE TIME
MY KID'S HERE NEXT YEAR.

11:35.444 --> 11:37.065
YEAH. DONE.

11:37.165 --> 11:39.487
ANYTHING FOR
BABY ASH.

11:42.409 --> 11:44.751
WAIT.
N-NEXT YEAR?

11:44.851 --> 11:46.912
DUDE.
DUDE, YEAH?

11:47.012 --> 11:48.794
YEAH.
JAYMEE'S PREGNANT.

11:48.894 --> 11:50.155
[CHUCKLING]
WHAT?

11:50.255 --> 11:52.036
OH, THAT'S
AMAZING, BRO!

11:52.136 --> 11:55.278
OH, MY GOSH, YOU'RE GONNA
BE AN AMAZING FATHER,

11:55.378 --> 11:57.880
AND--AND I'LL BE
THE WORLD'S
GREATEST UNCLE.

11:57.980 --> 12:01.843
I MEAN, FUNCLE JJ
IS OFFICIALLY
LOADING, HUH?

12:01.943 --> 12:03.805
[CHUCKLING]
LET'S GO, MAN.

12:03.905 --> 12:07.247
OH, MY GOSH.
ASHER, CHUCKLING: I KNOW.

12:07.347 --> 12:09.809
OH, AND IS IT COOL
IF WE KEEP HIS POSTER
IN THE PULPIT?

12:09.909 --> 12:11.771
PASTOR WEEKS: ABSOLUTELY.
SPENCER: OK.

12:11.871 --> 12:14.093
COOP: AND WE'RE GOOD
TO START AT 11 A.M.?
PASTOR WEEKS: WE ARE.

12:14.193 --> 12:16.855
COOP: THANK YOU, PASTOR WEEKS.
PASTOR WEEKS: IT'S
THE LEAST I CAN DO.

12:16.955 --> 12:19.457
BILLY WAS
THE PEOPLE'S CHAMP.

12:19.557 --> 12:22.058
MY SINCEREST CONDOLENCES,
MRS. BAKER.

12:22.158 --> 12:24.580
SO HOW MANY GUESTS
WERE YOU THINKING
FOR TOMORROW?

12:24.680 --> 12:28.443
SPENCER: OH, UH,
NO MORE THAN 15.
JUST FAMILY AND CLOSE FRIENDS.

12:30.044 --> 12:31.946
IS THERE A PROBLEM,
PASTOR?

12:32.046 --> 12:35.909
NONE WHATSOEVER.
UH, IT'S JUST, UM,

12:36.009 --> 12:38.631
RESPECTFULLY, BILLY WAS
BELOVED BY SO MANY.

12:38.731 --> 12:42.754
I MEAN, IF YOU'RE WORRIED
ABOUT THE SPACE, WE COULD
ALWAYS ADD MORE CHAIRS.

12:42.854 --> 12:45.156
THAT WAY,
WE CAN GIVE HIM
A BIGGER CELEBRATION.

12:45.256 --> 12:47.958
SPACE HAS NOTHING TO DO
WITH MY DECISION.

12:48.058 --> 12:50.960
IT'S SIMPLY
WHAT I WANT,

12:51.060 --> 12:53.482
RESPECTFULLY.
NOW, IF YOU DON'T MIND,

12:53.582 --> 12:56.904
I'D LOVE TO SEE
THE REST OF YOUR CHURCH.
PASTOR WEEKS: ABSOLUTELY.

13:00.547 --> 13:03.409
COOP: WHERE YOU GOING?
SPENCER: TO SEE WHAT ELSE
SHE NEEDS.

13:03.509 --> 13:07.452
WELL, THAT'S DOPE, YOU
BEING THERE FOR MS. BAKER,
BUT I GOT IT FROM HERE, MAN,

13:07.552 --> 13:10.815
SO GO AHEAD AND DO WHATEVER
YOU NEED TO DO FOR YOU.

13:10.915 --> 13:12.336
I AM DOING
WHAT I NEED TO DO.

13:12.436 --> 13:14.097
LIKE TAKING THE TIME
TO PROPERLY GRIEVE.

13:14.197 --> 13:16.299
SPENCER: COME ON, COOP.
COOP: BRO, YOU'VE BEEN

13:16.399 --> 13:19.141
MOVING NONSTOP SINCE
WE LOST COACH BAKER,

13:19.241 --> 13:21.543
OK, FROM ORGANISING
THE FUNERAL TO DOING

13:21.643 --> 13:24.385
THE PROGRAMS TO
CHECKING ON EVERYONE'S
MENTAL HEALTH.

13:24.485 --> 13:26.787
WHEN YOU GONNA STOP IN
AND CHECK ON YOURSELF?

13:26.887 --> 13:29.469
LISTEN, IN THE LAST
TWO YEARS, I LOST SHAWN,

13:29.569 --> 13:32.711
MY POPS, AND NOW COACH BAKER.
[COOP SIGHS]

13:32.811 --> 13:36.134
I GUESS YOU COULD SAY
I'M BUILT FOR MOMENTS
LIKE THIS.

13:43.859 --> 13:46.501
[ORGAN PLAYING]

13:55.828 --> 13:58.110
[SIGHS]

14:07.797 --> 14:10.199
[CELL PHONE VIBRATES]

14:11.600 --> 14:13.702
COOP: IS THAT SPENCER
ABOUT THE REPAST?

14:13.802 --> 14:16.784
UH, NO, BUT THERE'S ONE
AT THE HOUSE AFTER.

14:16.884 --> 14:18.225
WAIT.
WHAT'S A REPAST?

14:18.325 --> 14:20.747
IT'S LIKE
A FUNERAL AFTERPARTY.

14:20.847 --> 14:22.348
MRS. BAKER'S COOL
WITH THAT?

14:22.448 --> 14:24.710
APPARENTLY SO, AS LONG
AS IT'S JUST US.

14:24.810 --> 14:28.713
HEY...WHERE IS
SPENCER, ANYWAY?

14:28.813 --> 14:31.435
FEEL LIKE HE
HASN'T STOPPED
SINCE WE GOT HERE.

14:31.535 --> 14:35.658
HE HASN'T STOPPED
SINCE EVERYTHING HAPPENED.

14:40.702 --> 14:42.603
YOU OK, BABY?

14:42.703 --> 14:44.705
YEAH.

14:46.666 --> 14:49.368
SPENCER ALONZO JAMES,

14:49.468 --> 14:51.970
DON'T MAKE ME
ASK YOU AGAIN.

14:52.070 --> 14:54.372
I'M GOOD.
I'M GOOD, YOU KNOW.

14:54.472 --> 14:56.534
I JUST NEEDED A SECOND
BEFORE THINGS GET STARTED.

14:56.634 --> 14:59.156
WE SHOULD PROBABLY
GO TAKE OUR SEATS.
GRACE: YEAH.

15:03.999 --> 15:05.901
[SIGHS]

15:06.001 --> 15:08.423
HOW ARE YOU BOTH DOING?

15:08.523 --> 15:10.264
WE'RE OK, MOM.

15:10.364 --> 15:12.726
WE'RE JUST WORRIED
ABOUT YOU.

15:14.087 --> 15:16.909
I LOVE YOU BOTH
SO VERY MUCH.

15:17.009 --> 15:19.071
[SOBS]
YOU'RE THE BEST THING

15:19.171 --> 15:21.913
THAT YOUR DAD AND I
EVER DID.

15:22.013 --> 15:24.034
[CRYING]
I AM SO SORRY

15:24.134 --> 15:26.796
THAT YOU DIDN'T HAVE
MORE TIME WITH HIM.

15:26.896 --> 15:29.238
[SNIFFLES]

15:29.338 --> 15:31.820
[SIGHS]

15:35.663 --> 15:37.664
PASTOR WEEKS: IT'S TIME.

15:41.027 --> 15:47.932
CHOIR:
♪ WHEN JESUS IS ♪

15:48.032 --> 15:52.336
♪ MY PORTION ♪

15:52.436 --> 16:00.462
♪ A CONSTANT FRIEND ♪

16:00.562 --> 16:05.105
♪ IS HE ♪

16:05.205 --> 16:09.468
♪ HIS EYE IS ON... ♪

16:09.568 --> 16:12.511
PASTOR WEEKS: BILLY WAS
NOT ONLY A BELOVED FATHER,

16:12.611 --> 16:16.153
A WONDERFUL HUSBAND, COACH,
AND PRINCIPAL.

16:16.253 --> 16:18.955
I WANT EVERYBODY
TO BOW THEIR HEADS.

16:19.055 --> 16:21.838
PREACH: PRINCIPAL BAKER WAS
A GOOD FRIEND OF MINE

16:21.938 --> 16:25.000
AND HE PROVIDED AN OPPORTUNITY
FOR ME TO TAKE CARE
OF MY DAUGHTER,

16:25.100 --> 16:28.843
BUT WHAT I'M GONNA MISS
THE MOST IS, UH,

16:28.943 --> 16:30.684
THE DANCE BATTLES.

16:30.784 --> 16:33.046
[ALL CHUCKLING]

16:33.146 --> 16:36.629
[CHOIR'S SINGING ENDS]

16:38.950 --> 16:41.893
PASTOR WEEKS: HERE TO DO
A READING OF THE EULOGY

16:41.993 --> 16:44.454
WILL BE OLIVIA BAKER.

16:44.554 --> 16:47.056
AFTER THAT, WE'LL OPEN IT
UP FOR EVERYBODY

16:47.156 --> 16:49.878
TO SHARE A WORD
ABOUT BILLY.

17:01.487 --> 17:02.868
[SNIFFLES]

17:02.968 --> 17:04.830
[OLIVIA SIGHS]

17:04.930 --> 17:07.892
OLIVIA: UM...
[COOP COUGHS]

17:09.253 --> 17:12.035
M-MY DAD IS...

17:12.135 --> 17:14.137
[SNIFFLES]

17:15.778 --> 17:18.680
MY DAD IS...

17:18.780 --> 17:20.922
UH...

17:21.022 --> 17:23.564
A--A LOT OF THINGS.

17:23.664 --> 17:25.665
UM...

17:27.426 --> 17:30.008
HE WORE A LOT OF HATS

17:30.108 --> 17:33.011
AND, UM...

17:33.111 --> 17:35.493
I'M...SORRY.

17:35.593 --> 17:38.695
UM...
DENISE: TAKE YOUR TIME, BABY,

17:38.795 --> 17:39.896
TAKE YOUR TIME.

17:39.996 --> 17:43.158
[SNIFFLING]
UM...

17:44.679 --> 17:46.341
HEY, HEY.

17:46.441 --> 17:50.584
YOU ALL RIGHT?
I GOT YOU, ALL RIGHT?

17:50.684 --> 17:53.326
UM...

17:57.609 --> 18:01.512
SO, DID YOU GUYS KNOW--
AHEM--THE COLOUR BLUE...

18:01.612 --> 18:04.114
IS SUPPOSED
TO BRING PEACE,

18:04.214 --> 18:06.916
TRANQUILITY,
AND GOOD VIBES?

18:07.016 --> 18:12.040
I THINK THAT'S WHY IT'S
DAD'S FAVORITE COLOR.

18:12.140 --> 18:17.444
BUT, GUESSING, UH,
THAT YOU GUYS ALL LOVE
MY DAD AS MUCH AS WE DO,

18:17.544 --> 18:21.087
YOU ALREADY KNEW THAT.
[OLIVIA SNIFFLING]

18:21.187 --> 18:24.569
JORDAN:
I'D LOVE TO KNOW MORE.

18:24.669 --> 18:27.611
WE--WE'D LOVE TO,

18:27.711 --> 18:29.733
SO, UM,

18:29.833 --> 18:33.056
IF ANYONE HAS
ANYTHING THEY'D LIKE
TO SHARE ABOUT MY DAD,

18:33.156 --> 18:36.038
PLEASE...COME ON UP.

18:43.003 --> 18:46.125
YOU AIN'T GONNA GET
UP THERE AND SAY NOTHING?

19:05.019 --> 19:08.082
FINALLY
GETTING SOMETHING
IN YOUR STOMACH.

19:08.182 --> 19:10.403
THAT'S GOOD.

19:10.503 --> 19:13.806
GRACE: YOU SURE THIS REPAST
WON'T BE TOO MUCH FOR YOU?

19:13.906 --> 19:16.888
SO FAR, SO GOOD.

19:16.988 --> 19:20.891
SPENCER'S BEEN
AMAZING, BY THE WAY.
HE TOOK CARE OF EVERYTHING.

19:20.991 --> 19:23.773
SPEAKING OF MY FIRST-BORN,
HAVE YOU GUYS SEEN HIM?

19:23.873 --> 19:27.096
OH, HE--HE WENT TO LOU'S
TO PICK UP FOOD FOR ME.

19:27.196 --> 19:30.819
IT WAS BILLY'S...
FAVORITE.

19:30.919 --> 19:35.102
WOW. THAT'S THE FIRST TIME
I'VE SAID HIS NAME
WITHOUT CRYING,

19:35.202 --> 19:37.744
WHICH I WONDER WHAT
THAT SAYS ABOUT ME.

19:37.844 --> 19:40.306
IT JUST MEANS YOU'RE
A TINY STEP CLOSER
TO HEALING.

19:40.406 --> 19:43.428
LEAST THAT'S HOW IT WAS FOR ME
AFTER JASMYN'S MOM PASSED.

19:43.528 --> 19:46.150
DENISE: EXACTLY.
IT'S JUST YOUR HEAD
TELLING YOUR HEART

19:46.250 --> 19:48.512
YOU GOT THIS,
AND, HEY,

19:48.612 --> 19:50.854
WE GOT YOU.

19:57.178 --> 19:59.800
WILLIE: NICE JOB
ON THE EULOGY SAVE.

19:59.900 --> 20:01.762
THANKS, G.W.

20:01.862 --> 20:04.764
BLUE WAS
INDEED YOUR DAD'S
FAVORITE COLOR.

20:04.864 --> 20:08.487
FIREWORKS,
THE COLOUR BLUE,
AND BOYZ II MEN

20:08.587 --> 20:11.649
WERE PROBABLY
HIS 3 GREATEST LOVES...
[JORDAN CHUCKLES]

20:11.749 --> 20:14.371
WILLIE: UNTIL HE MET YOUR MOM.
[DOOR OPENS]

20:14.471 --> 20:16.093
SPENCER: OK, FOOD'S HERE.
PATIENCE: GREAT.

20:16.193 --> 20:19.455
GRACE: YAY!
CARTER: COME ON, COME ON.
SPENCER: HA HA!

20:19.555 --> 20:23.258
[OVERLAPPING CHATTER
AND LAUGHTER]

20:23.358 --> 20:28.021
SEEING PEOPLE LAUGHING
AND EATING AT A REPAST
IS NEVER EASY.

20:28.121 --> 20:33.045
IT SEEMS THEY'VE ALL
JUST...MOVED ON.

20:34.406 --> 20:36.948
YOU SEEM TO BE DOING OK.

20:37.048 --> 20:40.791
WE ALL FIND OUR PEACE
IN DIFFERENT WAYS.

20:40.891 --> 20:43.153
HOW DID YOU FIND YOURS?

20:43.253 --> 20:46.155
THE MOMENT THAT I
REALISED THAT YOUR DAD

20:46.255 --> 20:50.158
AND MY BELOVED MARY
WERE REUNITED.

20:50.258 --> 20:52.460
HMM.

20:55.062 --> 20:57.724
I BELIEVE SHE COMES
BEARING GIFTS FOR YOU.

20:57.824 --> 21:00.005
JORDAN: YEAH.
WILLIE: SEE YA.

21:00.105 --> 21:01.486
SEE YA.

21:01.586 --> 21:03.368
[DISTANT CHATTER
AND LAUGHTER CONTINUE]

21:03.468 --> 21:05.970
JORDAN: HI.
LAYLA: HI.

21:06.070 --> 21:08.652
WHAT WAS THAT ABOUT? HEH!
[JORDAN SIGHS]

21:08.752 --> 21:11.794
G.W.'s SECRET
TO, UH, MOVING ON...

21:13.075 --> 21:17.138
WHICH, ADMITTEDLY,
I AM...I AM NOWHERE NEAR.

21:17.238 --> 21:20.140
HEY, UM, YOU KNOW,
IF YOU JUST WANT
TO DUCK OUT,

21:20.240 --> 21:22.582
AND, LIKE,
TAKE SOME TIME
FOR YOURSELF,

21:22.682 --> 21:25.504
CLEAR YOUR HEAD,
I'LL COVER FOR YOU.

21:25.604 --> 21:27.506
NO, I'M NOT--
[SIGHS]

21:27.606 --> 21:29.147
I CAN'T BAIL ON LIV
AND MY MOM.

21:29.247 --> 21:32.830
HEY, I'M GONNA
MAKE SURE THEY'RE
FINE, OK? JUST GO.

21:32.930 --> 21:34.591
[CHATTER CONTINUES]

21:34.691 --> 21:38.074
JORDAN: THANK YOU, LAYLA.
LAYLA: YEAH.

21:38.174 --> 21:40.996
[DISTANT LAUGHTER]

21:41.096 --> 21:43.558
YOU KNOW, DARIUS HAS BEEN
KILLING IT AT WORK,

21:43.658 --> 21:45.559
SO WE'RE DEFINITELY
GONNA HOLD YOU DOWN
UNTIL YOU DECIDE

21:45.659 --> 21:48.822
YOU'RE READY TO COME BACK,
MS. BAKER.
[DOOR OPENS]

21:51.344 --> 21:53.865
WHAT IS JABARI
DOING HERE?

21:56.187 --> 21:57.849
I DON'T KNOW,
BUT I'LL HANDLE IT.

21:57.949 --> 22:00.010
PATIENCE: YEAH,
WHY DON'T WE GET YOU SOME FOOD

22:00.110 --> 22:02.472
OR SOMETHING?
GET SOMETHING, GET SOMETHING.

22:06.475 --> 22:08.336
COOP:
HEY, LOOK, UM,

22:08.436 --> 22:11.219
BRO, YOU CAN'T BE HERE.
YOU GOTTA BOUNCE.

22:11.319 --> 22:14.221
HE WILL. HE WILL.
HE JUST PAYING
HIS RESPECTS. COME ON.

22:14.321 --> 22:16.222
[ALUMINUM FOIL CRINKLES]
LAURA: UM,

22:16.322 --> 22:18.704
I DIDN'T ORDER
DAMN MASHED POTATOES.

22:18.804 --> 22:21.186
I ORDERED
SWEET POTATOES!

22:21.286 --> 22:23.187
UM, I--I CHECKED
THE CONTAINER.

22:23.287 --> 22:26.030
[SIGHS]
HOW HARD IS IT FOR LOU'S
TO GET THE ORDER RIGHT?!

22:26.130 --> 22:28.792
- YO, WE HAVE
OTHER FOOD, MRS. BA--
- I DON'T WANT OTHER FOOD!

22:28.892 --> 22:32.194
OK.
[SETS DOWN DISH]
I'LL JUST GO BACK.

22:32.294 --> 22:34.516
LAURA: THAT WON'T BE NECESSARY.
DENISE: ARE YOU SURE?

22:34.616 --> 22:36.437
'CAUSE IT'S RIGHT
AROUND THE CORNER.
HE CAN JUST GO BACK.

22:36.537 --> 22:38.679
[ECHOING]
SPENCER: I'LL JUST GO BACK.
DENISE: HE CAN JUST GO BACK.

22:38.779 --> 22:40.520
BILLY: I HAVE TO.
SPENCER: IT'S ALL GOOD,
MRS. BAKER.

22:40.620 --> 22:43.242
I CAN JUST GO BACK.
LAURA: NO ONE IS
GOING BACK, OK?!

22:43.342 --> 22:46.585
NO ONE IS GOING BACK!

22:51.829 --> 22:53.830
[MOUTHING WORDS]

22:55.031 --> 22:57.033
[SIGHS]

23:09.682 --> 23:12.224
JORDAN:
HEY, THINK FAST, OLD MAN!

23:12.324 --> 23:13.585
BILLY: OOH. AWOO!
JORDAN: HA HA!

23:13.685 --> 23:15.587
- "OLD MAN"? HA HA!
- YUP.

23:15.687 --> 23:18.229
- OOH, THAT'S A LITTLE WOBBLY!
- HA HA!

23:18.329 --> 23:20.470
JORDAN: AND YOU'RE THE ONE WHO
TAUGHT ME HOW TO THROW A SPIRAL.

23:20.570 --> 23:23.052
BILLY: OH.
NEVER HAD YOUR ARM, THOUGH.

23:31.058 --> 23:33.280
YOU KNOW...

23:33.380 --> 23:36.202
THE ONLY PAIN
THAT MATCHES
LOSING A CHILD

23:36.302 --> 23:38.964
IS LOSING...
A SOULMATE.

23:39.064 --> 23:41.606
AND, SADLY, I'M
THE ONLY PERSON
IN THIS ROOM

23:41.706 --> 23:44.248
THAT'S
EXPERIENCED BOTH.

23:44.348 --> 23:47.711
I CAN'T EVEN IMAGINE WHAT
YOU ARE GOING THROUGH.

23:49.031 --> 23:51.613
LEAST YOU GOT TO SAY
GOOD-BYE TO MARY.

23:51.713 --> 23:54.255
I'M NOT TRYING
TO COMPARE THE TWO.

23:54.355 --> 23:58.198
I'M JUST TRYING
TO BE THERE FOR
MY DAUGHTER-IN-LAW.

24:04.843 --> 24:08.146
I WAS DOING SO GOOD,
TOO, YOU KNOW? I...
[INHALES DEEPLY]

24:08.246 --> 24:11.829
[SIGHS]
I--I SAID BILLY'S NAME
WITHOUT GETTING CHOKED UP,

24:11.929 --> 24:14.711
BUT THEN THERE'S JABARI,
JUST IN MY HOUSE.

24:14.811 --> 24:17.233
THIS ISN'T
HIS FAULT, LAURA.

24:17.333 --> 24:19.634
BILLY CHOSE

24:19.734 --> 24:22.156
TO GO BACK ON THAT BUS.

24:22.256 --> 24:24.678
THAT 17-YEAR-OLD BOY WATCHED

24:24.778 --> 24:27.120
HIS MENTOR SACRIFICE
HIS LIFE FOR HIM.

24:27.220 --> 24:29.522
NO CHILD SHOULD HAVE
TO CARRY THAT.

24:29.622 --> 24:32.844
THE ANGER YOU'RE
FEELING HAS NOTHING
TO DO WITH THIS KID.

24:32.944 --> 24:36.687
I KNOW, BUT THEN,
WHEN I SAW HIM, ALL I COULD
THINK ABOUT WAS BILLY.

24:36.787 --> 24:40.410
TALK TO HIM.
HE'S JUST A KID,
AND HE'S HURTING.

24:40.510 --> 24:43.332
I KNOW HE IS.
[SNIFFLES]

24:43.432 --> 24:45.934
WE ALL ARE.

24:46.034 --> 24:48.036
EXACTLY.

24:50.597 --> 24:52.839
[LAURA SIGHS]

24:54.080 --> 24:55.701
HOW'S MY MOM DOING?

24:55.801 --> 24:58.704
[SIGHS]
SHE'S FIGURING
THINGS OUT.

24:58.804 --> 25:02.026
WE JUST HAVE TO MOVE
AT HER SPEED.

25:02.126 --> 25:04.128
YEAH.

25:07.090 --> 25:10.773
[DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

25:13.455 --> 25:16.237
JJ: HEY.
OLIVIA: HEY.

25:16.337 --> 25:18.598
UH...

25:18.698 --> 25:21.681
ARE YOU JUST NOW
GETTING HERE?

25:21.781 --> 25:23.842
UH, YEAH, YEAH.
MY BAD.

25:23.942 --> 25:26.845
I--I HAD TO DROP ASHER
AT HIS DOC APPOINTMENT

25:26.945 --> 25:30.287
FOR HIS ARM AND THEN STOP
BY THE HOUSE FOR A SEC.

25:30.387 --> 25:32.249
NO WORRIES.

25:32.349 --> 25:35.211
THERE'S PLENTY OF FOOD
IN THE FRIDGE.
HELP YOURSELF.

25:35.311 --> 25:37.312
AWESOME.

25:38.954 --> 25:40.995
ARE YOU DRUNK?

25:42.716 --> 25:45.218
I CAN SMELL
THE BOURBON.

25:45.318 --> 25:47.420
OK, YES,
I HAD A FEW SIPS,

25:47.520 --> 25:49.662
BUT I PROMISE I'M NOT--
OLIVIA: ARE YOU SERIOUS?

25:49.762 --> 25:52.704
OF ALL THE DAYS
TO DO THIS, YOU'RE
GONNA DO THIS TODAY?

25:52.804 --> 25:54.866
LAYLA: HEY, WHAT'S GOING ON?
OLIVIA: JJ's DRUNK.

25:54.966 --> 25:57.067
JJ: NO, I'M NOT.
OLIVIA: IT DOESN'T MATTER.

25:57.167 --> 26:00.270
I CANNOT WITH
THE LIES RIGHT NOW,
SO PLEASE JUST GO, JJ,

26:00.370 --> 26:02.111
NOW.

26:02.211 --> 26:04.893
YOU'RE
LITERALLY TRASH.

26:16.502 --> 26:18.503
[SIGHS]

26:23.307 --> 26:26.169
JABARI: THANKS FOR CALLING.
JORDAN: YEAH.

26:26.269 --> 26:30.572
I HEARD WHAT HAPPENED
WITH MY MOM AND...FIGURED
I SHOULD REACH OUT.

26:30.672 --> 26:32.894
I SHOULDN'T
HAVE COME INSIDE.

26:32.994 --> 26:34.895
YOU WERE JUST PAYING
YOUR RESPECTS,

26:34.995 --> 26:36.977
AND I KNOW HOW HARD
THAT MUST HAVE BEEN.

26:37.077 --> 26:39.059
SPEAKS TO WHO YOU ARE
AS A PERSON,

26:39.159 --> 26:41.841
AND IT EXPLAINS WHAT
MY DAD SAW IN YOU.

26:43.322 --> 26:46.224
JABARI, I NEED YOU
TO HEAR ME.

26:46.324 --> 26:49.106
WHAT HAPPENED
TO MY DAD

26:49.206 --> 26:51.228
WAS NOT YOUR FAULT.

26:51.328 --> 26:54.470
TRUTHFULLY,
HE WOULD HAVE DONE THAT
FOR ANY OF HIS PLAYERS.

26:54.570 --> 26:56.472
[SIGHS]

26:56.572 --> 26:59.354
THAT MEANS A LOT, J.

26:59.454 --> 27:00.995
SALUTE.

27:01.095 --> 27:03.096
YEAH.

27:05.018 --> 27:08.601
MAN, YOUR DAD TAUGHT ME
EVERYTHING I KNOW...

27:08.701 --> 27:12.323
FROM THE CLASSROOM
TO THE FOOTBALL FIELD.

27:12.423 --> 27:13.925
YEAH.

27:14.025 --> 27:16.446
YEAH, THAT FIELD WAS
HIS SANCTUARY.

27:16.546 --> 27:18.408
BIG FACTS.

27:18.508 --> 27:21.090
HE HAD PLANNED
TO COME BACK AND MAKE

27:21.190 --> 27:23.452
THE OFFICIAL ANNOUNCEMENT
ON BILLY BAKER FIELD

27:23.552 --> 27:26.374
THAT HE WAS STAYING
AT SOUTH CRENSHAW.

27:26.474 --> 27:28.776
WAIT. FOR REAL?

27:28.876 --> 27:31.418
IT WAS ONE OF
THE LAST THINGS HE SAID

27:31.518 --> 27:34.780
TO ME AND MY TEAMMATES
ON THAT BUS...

27:34.880 --> 27:37.622
AND HE WAS GONNA
INVITE EVERYBODY, MAN:

27:37.722 --> 27:39.784
EX-PLAYERS,
CURRENT PLAYERS,

27:39.884 --> 27:42.306
HELL, EVERYONE
IN THE COMMUNITY.

27:42.406 --> 27:44.948
HE WANTED US TO KNOW
THAT HE WASN'T JUST

27:45.048 --> 27:49.431
COMMITTED TO THE SCHOOL,
BUT...TO THE COMMUNITY, TOO.

27:49.531 --> 27:51.833
HE WAS DOUBLING DOWN
ON SOUTH CRENSHAW,

27:51.933 --> 27:54.575
MAN, FOR GOOD.

27:56.016 --> 27:58.017
HMM.

28:01.980 --> 28:03.882
JORDAN: HEY.
LAYLA: HEY.

28:03.982 --> 28:06.444
I WANT TO THROW MY DAD
A CELEBRATION.

28:06.544 --> 28:09.006
OK, YEAH. WHAT KIND
OF CELEBRATION AND WHEN?

28:09.106 --> 28:10.847
TONIGHT,
BILLY BAKER FIELD.

28:10.947 --> 28:13.009
- TONIGHT?
- YES, MY DAD WAS PLANNING

28:13.109 --> 28:14.810
ON TELLING THE COMMUNITY
THAT HE WAS STAYING

28:14.910 --> 28:17.292
AT SOUTH CRENSHAW,
BUT HE NEVER HAD
THE CHANCE, AND I KNOW

28:17.392 --> 28:20.294
THAT MY MOM WANTED
SOME PRIVATE FUNERAL,
BUT I JUST FEEL

28:20.394 --> 28:23.777
LIKE THE COMMUNITY
NEEDS THEIR CHANCE TO
CELEBRATE MY DAD, TOO,

28:23.877 --> 28:27.179
CELEBRATE THE MAN
THAT HE WAS, OK?
I MEAN, WE ALL DO.

28:27.279 --> 28:30.862
RIGHT. UM, I MEAN, I GUESS
WE CAN GET THE VORTEX
TO PITCH IN AND HELP.

28:30.962 --> 28:33.304
I JUST--I HAVE
ONE QUESTION:

28:33.404 --> 28:35.586
ARE YOU SURE YOUR MOM'S
GONNA BE DOWN WITH THIS?

28:35.686 --> 28:38.548
I'M NOT, UM, WHICH...

28:38.648 --> 28:41.190
WHICH IS WHY WE'RE
NOT GONNA TELL HER.

28:41.290 --> 28:44.512
MMM. UM, AND YOU'RE SURE
YOU'RE OK WITH THAT?

28:44.612 --> 28:46.474
YES, I AM.

28:46.574 --> 28:49.676
LOOK, LAYLA, THIS IS ME
TRYING TO RESPECT
MY MOM'S WISHES,

28:49.776 --> 28:52.578
BUT HONOUR WHAT
MY DAD WANTED, TOO.

28:53.779 --> 28:55.981
LAYLA: OK.
JORDAN: GREAT.

28:58.262 --> 29:02.886
DENISE: SO, YOU THINK
YOU'RE READY TO HAVE
THIS CONVERSATION WITH JABARI?

29:02.986 --> 29:04.687
[SIGHS]

29:04.787 --> 29:08.690
I DON'T KNOW
IF I CAN DO IT...

29:08.790 --> 29:11.773
BUT I FEEL LIKE I
HAVE TO TRY.

29:11.873 --> 29:14.595
GRACE: I'M PROUD OF YOU.
LAURA: THANKS.

29:17.517 --> 29:19.859
THE HOUSE IS
AWFULLY QUIET.

29:19.959 --> 29:22.421
SOMETHING'S UP.
DENISE: HEH!

29:22.521 --> 29:25.383
ISN'T IT FUNNY HOW
WE SAY THAT, NO MATTER
HOW OLD OUR KIDS ARE?

29:25.483 --> 29:27.504
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

29:27.604 --> 29:31.347
OK, WHAT ARE YOU TWO
NOT TELLING ME?

29:31.447 --> 29:34.630
THE KIDS ARE PLANNING
A CELEBRATION
FOR BILLY,

29:34.730 --> 29:37.352
TONIGHT AT
THE BILLY BAKER FIELD,

29:37.452 --> 29:40.674
SOMETHING
FOR THE WHOLE COMMUNITY.
LAURA: AND NO ONE TOLD ME?

29:40.774 --> 29:43.276
THEY DIDN'T KNOW IF YOU'D
BE READY FOR IT, AND

29:43.376 --> 29:45.678
THEY STILL WANTED TO HONOUR
THEIR FATHER'S WISHES.

29:45.778 --> 29:48.440
GRACE: AND IF YOU ARE
READY, OBVIOUSLY,

29:48.540 --> 29:51.542
THEY WOULD LOVE FOR YOU
TO BE THERE.
[LAURA SIGHS]

29:52.823 --> 29:56.666
WELL, THEY'RE RIGHT.
I'M NOT READY.

29:59.668 --> 30:01.570
[DOOR OPENS]

30:01.670 --> 30:03.531
DILLON: MMM.

30:03.631 --> 30:06.534
GOT YOUR TEXT.
WHAT'S GOING ON?
WE COULDN'T TALK AT HOME?

30:06.634 --> 30:09.856
JORDAN'S COOKING UP
A DOPE IDEA OUTSIDE
ON THE FOOTBALL FIELD,

30:09.956 --> 30:15.000
BUT I FIGURED I'D STEAL
A COUPLE MINUTES WITH YOU
BEFORE CHAOS DESCENDS.

30:16.441 --> 30:18.302
[GRUNTS]
WHAT'S UP?

30:18.402 --> 30:20.504
[SIGHS]
THANK YOU.

30:20.604 --> 30:22.505
FOR WHAT?

30:22.605 --> 30:24.507
FOR SHOWING UP FOR ME.

30:24.607 --> 30:26.508
SPENCE,
YOU'RE MY BROTHER.

30:26.608 --> 30:29.891
I'M ALWAYS
GONNA BE HERE.

30:32.573 --> 30:35.795
THAT VOICEMAIL THAT
BILLY LEFT...

30:35.895 --> 30:39.078
THE ONE I KEEP
LISTENING TO?

30:39.178 --> 30:41.680
I DIDN'T MISS
THE CALL THAT DAY.

30:41.780 --> 30:44.122
I DECLINED IT

30:44.222 --> 30:46.603
'CAUSE
I WAS STILL ANGRY
AT HIM FOR TAKING

30:46.703 --> 30:49.446
THE HEAD-COACH GIG
AT GAU.

30:49.546 --> 30:51.607
I'D GIVE ANYTHING

30:51.707 --> 30:54.249
TO GET
THAT MOMENT BACK,

30:54.349 --> 30:56.611
BUT, UH, TIME DOESN'T
RUN BACKWARDS, SO NOW

30:56.711 --> 30:59.253
I STAY RUNNING
FOR EVERYBODY
THAT NEEDS COACH

30:59.353 --> 31:01.775
RIGHT NOW
AND CAN'T HAVE HIM.

31:01.875 --> 31:03.776
I GOTTA BE THERE
FOR THEM.

31:03.876 --> 31:06.899
AND YOU STAY RUNNING
BECAUSE IF YOU STOP,

31:06.999 --> 31:10.521
YOUR MIND'S GONNA
TAKE YOU RIGHT BACK
TO DECLINING THAT CALL.

31:11.722 --> 31:15.625
WHEN'D YOU GET
SO SMART, MAN?

31:15.725 --> 31:19.628
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACH]
OLIVIA: SEE THE JAMES BROTHERS
GOT THE INVITE, TOO?

31:19.728 --> 31:23.631
DILLON: UH, ALL I KNOW IS
THAT APPARENTLY JORDAN IS
PLANNING SOMETHING DOPE,

31:23.731 --> 31:28.134
AND NOW SEEMS LIKE
A GOOD IDEA TO SEE
IF HE NEEDS HELP WITH THAT.

31:29.375 --> 31:32.878
I JUST, UM, I WANTED
TO SAY THANK YOU.

31:32.978 --> 31:35.720
I MEAN, YOU ARE
THE GLUE THAT KEPT

31:35.820 --> 31:38.522
MY FAMILY TOGETHER
THIS WEEK, AND...

31:38.622 --> 31:41.565
I MEAN, ESPECIALLY
WITH MY MOM AND
THE FUNERAL STUFF,

31:41.665 --> 31:43.886
IT JUST MEANS A LOT.

31:43.986 --> 31:46.488
I'M JUST TRYING
TO DO MY PART,

31:46.588 --> 31:49.891
HELPING Y'ALL
FIND Y'ALL FOOTING
IN THIS NEW NORMAL.

31:49.991 --> 31:53.293
I DON'T KNOW THAT IT
WILL EVER FEEL NORMAL.

31:53.393 --> 31:57.657
- NO.
- I THINK THAT'S WHY
I COULDN'T FINISH MY EULOGY,

31:57.757 --> 31:59.818
'CAUSE MY DAD IS...

31:59.918 --> 32:02.820
A LOT OF THINGS, BUT...

32:02.920 --> 32:08.144
MOST IMPORTANTLY,
HE WAS MY EVERYTHING.

32:08.244 --> 32:11.227
HOW AM I SUPPOSED
TO PUT THAT INTO WORDS?
[CHUCKLES]

32:11.327 --> 32:15.510
HMM...KINDA SOUNDS
LIKE YOU JUST DID.

32:15.610 --> 32:16.991
[CHUCKLES]

32:17.091 --> 32:18.512
YEAH.

32:18.612 --> 32:21.194
JORDAN: YO! HEY.

32:21.294 --> 32:24.316
BROUGHT A FEW FRIENDS
WITH ME.

32:24.416 --> 32:26.518
[CHUCKLES]
FRAUSTO.

32:26.618 --> 32:29.520
SPENCER: WHAT'S GOOD, MY BOY?
THANK YOU FOR COMING, MAN.

32:29.620 --> 32:31.962
COME ON, SPENCE.
YOU KNOW WE HAD
TO PULL UP FOR COACH.

32:32.062 --> 32:34.164
SPENCER: OH, YEAH.
ASHER: GOAT OF ALL COACHES.

32:34.264 --> 32:38.167
COOP: FACTS.
DEFINITELY A DOPE WAY TO
CELEBRATE HIS GREATNESS.

32:38.267 --> 32:40.408
WAIT.
WHAT HAPPENED TO LAYLA?

32:40.508 --> 32:43.451
SHE IS...PICKING UP
A LAST-MINUTE NECESSITY.

32:43.551 --> 32:46.333
JORDAN: HMM. OK. SO, UH,
REAL QUICK, UH, WE STILL
HAVE A FEW MORE PEOPLE

32:46.433 --> 32:48.695
ARRIVING
AND SOME SETTING-UP TO DO
ON THE FOOTBALL FIELD,

32:48.795 --> 32:51.337
BUT I JUST WANTED
TO SAY THANK YOU ALL

32:51.437 --> 32:53.538
FOR MAKING THIS POSSIBLE.
HEH!

32:53.638 --> 32:55.700
THIS SCHOOL IS, UM,

32:55.800 --> 32:58.342
IT'S WHERE MY DAD BROKE
RECORDS AS A PLAYER

32:58.442 --> 33:00.984
AND--AND WON GAMES
AS A COACH...

33:01.084 --> 33:04.066
[SIGHS]
INCLUDING A CHAMPIONSHIP
GAME LAST YEAR

33:04.166 --> 33:06.668
THAT I CAN FINALLY ADMIT--
FRAUSTO: OH, SO NOW

33:06.768 --> 33:09.270
YOU WANT TO GIVE US
OUR FLOWERS? OK.
[ALL CHUCKLE]

33:09.370 --> 33:12.592
BUT--BUT IN ALL
SERIOUSNESS, OK, UM,

33:12.692 --> 33:15.234
WE ALWAYS HEAR
ABOUT HOW MUCH,

33:15.334 --> 33:18.237
YOU KNOW, MY DAD MEANT
TO YOU GUYS, UM...

33:18.337 --> 33:20.679
BUT YOU GUYS
HAVE NO IDEA

33:20.779 --> 33:23.361
HOW MUCH YOU
MEANT TO MY DAD, UM,

33:23.461 --> 33:25.882
SO LET'S GET
TO THE FIELD AND GET

33:25.982 --> 33:28.644
THIS SMALL CELEBRATION
UNDERWAY, HUH?

33:28.744 --> 33:30.566
PREACH: SMALL?

33:30.666 --> 33:34.389
WAIT TILL YOU SEE THE CROWD
FORMING OUTSIDE.

33:49.840 --> 33:51.842
[SIGHS]

34:21.624 --> 34:23.085
[CLEARS THROAT]

34:23.185 --> 34:26.408
[SNIFFLES]
WILLIE, WHAT ARE
YOU DOING HERE?

34:26.508 --> 34:29.410
I WAS IN THE
NEIGHBORHOOD AND FIGURED
WHY THE HELL NOT?

34:29.510 --> 34:32.052
I LOVE WHAT YOU'VE
DONE WITH THE PLACE.

34:32.152 --> 34:35.254
THE PICTURES BILLY
USED TO SEND ME DON'T
DO IT JUSTICE.

34:35.354 --> 34:38.737
LAURA: HE SENT YOU PICTURES?
WILLIE: ALL THE TIME.

34:38.837 --> 34:41.619
WE USED TO TALK
ON THE PHONE
EVERY WEDNESDAY.

34:41.719 --> 34:44.621
WHEN DID THIS HAPPEN?

34:44.721 --> 34:46.343
MONTHS AGO.

34:46.443 --> 34:49.985
THE BEST THING
THAT EVER HAPPENED
FOR MY SON AND I.

34:50.085 --> 34:54.689
WE'D END EACH CALL
WITH..."I LOVE YOU."

34:59.052 --> 35:02.374
I GUESS THAT'S...
[SIGHS]

35:03.615 --> 35:07.118
WHY YOU'RE DEALING
WITH HIS DEATH SO WELL.

35:07.218 --> 35:11.641
YEAH. YOU KNOW, MARY
AND I THOUGHT WE'D BE
IN THIS HOUSE FOREVER,

35:11.741 --> 35:13.963
CHASING THE SUN TOGETHER.

35:14.063 --> 35:16.765
ONCE I LOST HER,
I LOST HOPE IN LOVE

35:16.865 --> 35:19.487
UNTIL YOU AND BILLY
MOVED IN.

35:19.587 --> 35:22.089
YOU BROUGHT LOVE
BACK INTO THIS HOME;

35:22.189 --> 35:26.072
NOT JUST THE TWO
OF YOU, BUT JORDAN
AND OLIVIA, TOO.

35:27.913 --> 35:30.816
I AM GUESSING THAT YOU KNEW
ABOUT TONIGHT, TOO?

35:30.916 --> 35:34.138
I WAS THE FIRST ONE
JORDAN REACHED OUT TO.

35:34.238 --> 35:36.660
YOU SHOULD BE
MY PLUS-ONE.

35:36.760 --> 35:39.262
OH, I...

35:39.362 --> 35:42.945
I DON'T THINK
I'M READY FOR THAT.
WILLIE: OF COURSE YOU ARE.

35:43.045 --> 35:46.147
YOU ARE THE MAIN REASON
BILLY IS SO EMBRACED.

35:46.247 --> 35:50.230
WHEN YOU MOVED BACK HERE,
YOU GAVE HIM BACK
TO HIS COMMUNITY.

35:50.330 --> 35:54.313
ALL THEY WANT
TO DO IS GIVE BACK TO YOU

35:54.413 --> 35:56.495
AND SAY THANK YOU.

36:00.858 --> 36:03.320
[OVERLAPPING CHATTER]

36:03.420 --> 36:04.801
LAYLA: THANK YOU
AGAIN FOR DOING THIS.

36:04.901 --> 36:07.443
COACH BAKER REALLY WAS
YOUR BIGGEST FAN.

36:07.543 --> 36:11.466
I'M JUST GLAD TO BE HERE
FOR YOU ALL. IT'S A VERY
SPECIAL CELEBRATION.

36:14.148 --> 36:17.330
GOOD EVENING, EVERYBODY.
UH, MY NAME IS SHAWN STOCKMAN.

36:17.430 --> 36:19.172
[CHEERING AND WHISTLING]

36:19.272 --> 36:21.373
SHAWN: COACH,
THIS IS FOR YOU.

36:21.473 --> 36:24.155
[GUITAR PLAYING A BALLAD]

36:30.760 --> 36:33.703
♪ THERE'S A REASON ♪

36:33.803 --> 36:36.265
♪ FOR EVERYTHING ♪

36:36.365 --> 36:40.508
♪ AND A PURPOSE FOR EVERYONE ♪

36:40.608 --> 36:43.910
♪ LIKE THE SEASONS ♪

36:44.010 --> 36:46.512
♪ WERE MADE TO CHANGE ♪

36:46.612 --> 36:50.916
♪ THAT'S WHY WE
APPRECIATE EACH ONE ♪

36:51.016 --> 36:55.919
♪ THERE'S ROADS WE ALL
MUST TRAVEL ♪

36:56.019 --> 37:00.403
♪ THOUGH THE DESTINATION
IS THE SAME ♪

37:00.503 --> 37:03.405
[CELL PHONE VIBRATES]
♪ BUT THE FOOTPRINTS ♪

37:03.505 --> 37:07.008
♪ WE LEAVE BEHIND'S
WHAT MAKE ♪

37:07.108 --> 37:11.211
♪ THE JOURNEY WORTH
ALL THE PAIN ♪

37:11.311 --> 37:17.535
♪ NOW LISTEN,
DON'T YOU CRY ♪

37:17.635 --> 37:21.739
♪ WIPE THE TEARS AWAY
FROM YOUR EYES ♪

37:21.839 --> 37:24.661
♪ I'M ALL RIGHT ♪

37:24.761 --> 37:27.783
♪ IT'S OK ♪

37:27.883 --> 37:30.585
♪ MY WORK IS ALL DONE... ♪

37:30.685 --> 37:32.687
JABARI.

37:33.968 --> 37:36.229
WILLIE: I'LL BE ON THE FIELD.
LAURA: OK.

37:36.329 --> 37:40.232
MS. BAKER, LOOK,
I--I AM SO SORRY.
I NE--

37:40.332 --> 37:42.374
ME FIRST.

37:45.857 --> 37:48.639
BILLY GAVE UP
HIS LIFE FOR YOU,

37:48.739 --> 37:51.080
AND NOW I NEED
YOU TO TAKE

37:51.180 --> 37:53.082
EVERYTHING
HE TAUGHT YOU

37:53.182 --> 37:56.605
AND MAKE THE MOST
OF THE LIFE THAT
YOU STILL HAVE.

37:56.705 --> 37:59.006
CAN YOU
PROMISE ME THAT?

37:59.106 --> 38:01.568
YES, MA'AM.
YOU--YOU GOT MY WORD.

38:01.668 --> 38:04.170
I NEED MORE THAN
YOUR WORD.

38:04.270 --> 38:06.772
I NEED
YOUR COMMITMENT,

38:06.872 --> 38:09.614
YOUR DEDICATION,

38:09.714 --> 38:12.456
AND PROOF
THAT YOU'RE MAKING

38:12.556 --> 38:14.818
AN IMPACT...

38:14.918 --> 38:17.840
BECAUSE THAT'S HOW
BILLY WOULD DO IT.

38:19.081 --> 38:21.623
DON'T LET US DOWN.

38:21.723 --> 38:23.585
I WON'T.

38:23.685 --> 38:26.767
[GUITAR-PLAYING RESUMES]

38:29.809 --> 38:31.711
[SONG ENDS]

38:31.811 --> 38:33.812
[SCATTERED CHEERING]

38:40.377 --> 38:42.319
JORDAN: OH.

38:42.419 --> 38:45.361
OLIVIA: WHAT'S--WHAT'S--
WHAT'S THIS?
WILLIE: FIREWORKS.

38:45.461 --> 38:48.003
IT AIN'T A CELEBRATION
FOR BILLY WITHOUT THESE.

38:48.103 --> 38:51.966
WOW, G.W.,
THIS--THIS IS R--

38:52.066 --> 38:55.649
UM, AHEM. MOM. MOM, LOOK,
I--I CAN EXPLAIN.
EVERYTHING--

38:55.749 --> 38:57.750
LAURA: IT'S OK.

39:00.312 --> 39:02.314
OK.

39:10.560 --> 39:12.862
A WISE MAN...

39:12.962 --> 39:15.624
ONCE SAID THAT LIFE...

39:15.724 --> 39:18.626
IS A SERIES OF LOSSES,

39:18.726 --> 39:21.628
BUT LOSSES BREED
LESSONS AND...

39:21.728 --> 39:24.630
LESSONS CREATE BLESSINGS.

39:24.730 --> 39:28.053
THAT WISE MAN WAS
MY HUSBAND.

39:31.175 --> 39:33.077
I HONESTLY DIDN'T
BELIEVE HIM

39:33.177 --> 39:35.078
TILL JUST NOW
BECAUSE FOR

39:35.178 --> 39:37.880
THE PAST FEW DAYS,
I'VE BEEN

39:37.980 --> 39:41.123
PUSHING BACK ON THE IDEA
OF COMMUNITY

39:41.223 --> 39:45.286
AND SHARING MY GRIEF
FOR BILLY WITH YOU.

39:45.386 --> 39:50.009
BUT TRUTHFULLY, I WOULDN'T
BE HERE WITHOUT YOU,

39:50.109 --> 39:53.732
AND I REALISE THAT I CAN'T
MOVE FORWARD WITHOUT YOU.

39:53.832 --> 39:55.093
[SNIFFLES]

39:55.193 --> 39:57.575
BILLY IS...
[SIGHS]

39:57.675 --> 39:59.676
MY LOSS...

40:00.597 --> 40:02.939
THE GREATEST LOSS,

40:03.039 --> 40:05.941
MY PAIN, MY LESSON.

40:06.041 --> 40:09.504
[SIGHS]
BUT YOU...

40:09.604 --> 40:14.608
I'M SO GRATEFUL THAT ALL OF YOU
HAVE TURNED INTO MY BLESSING.

40:15.849 --> 40:18.090
THANK YOU.

40:28.938 --> 40:31.440
[FIREWORKS WHISTLING
AND BOOMING]

40:31.540 --> 40:34.462
[EMILY ROWED'S
"LET ME HURT" PLAYING]

40:37.024 --> 40:38.886
♪ I AM UNFOLDING ♪

40:38.986 --> 40:42.629
♪ I AM NOT HOLDING ON ♪

40:44.150 --> 40:46.051
♪ SHATTERED IN PIECES ♪

40:46.151 --> 40:50.094
♪ I AM THE BROKEN ONE ♪

40:50.194 --> 40:53.737
♪ IF YOU ONLY KNEW
THE CHAOS ♪

40:53.837 --> 40:56.739
♪ INSIDE MY HEAD ♪

40:56.839 --> 40:58.701
♪ WISH THAT I COULD RUN ♪

40:58.801 --> 41:01.022
BILLY: SPENCER JAMES?
EMILY: ♪ BUT I'M JUST NOT ♪

41:01.122 --> 41:04.585
♪ READY YET ♪
BILLY: MY BAD. DIDN'T MEAN
TO, UH, STARTLE YOU.

41:04.685 --> 41:06.747
EMILY: ♪ JUST LET ME HURT ♪
BILLY: BILLY BAKER,

41:06.847 --> 41:09.269
VARSITY COACH, BEVERLY HIGH.
EMILY: ♪ A LITTLE LONGER ♪

41:09.369 --> 41:11.550
SPENCER: BEVERLY HILLS, HUH?
BILLY: YES, SIR.

